            <p>H. Law Firm (恒. 律师事务所) is headquartered in Markham, Ontario — one of Canada's cities with the highest proportion of Chinese-Canadian residents. Principal lawyer Miao He (何淼) leads the firm and provides <strong>full Mandarin family law services</strong> tailored to the GTA's Chinese-Canadian community. She holds dual licences from the Law Society of Ontario (#83315K) and the China Bar Association.</p>
          </div>

          <h2>Family Law Services We Provide in Markham</h2>
          <p>Family law cases in the Markham Chinese-Canadian community frequently involve cross-border assets, authentication of marriages registered in China, and property division spanning two legal systems. Miao He holds dual licences in Ontario and China — making her one of the very few lawyers who can handle these matters as a single point of contact.</p>

          <h3>Divorce Litigation</h3>
          <p>Ontario divorce requires either one year of separation or grounds such as adultery or physical/mental cruelty. Miao He assists clients through both uncontested and contested divorce, handling Equalization of Net Family Property, Spousal Support, and all child-related matters.</p>

          <h3>Child Custody &amp; Access</h3>
          <p>Ontario courts decide custody based on the Best Interests of the Child. Miao He represents clients seeking primary decision-making responsibility, joint arrangements, and urgent situations — including preventing a child from being removed from Ontario.</p>

          <h3>Marriage Contract (Prenuptial Agreement)</h3>
          <p>Marriage contracts are increasingly common in Markham's Chinese-Canadian community, particularly to protect property held in China, family business interests, and assets gifted by parents. Miao He drafts in both Chinese and English, ensuring the agreement will withstand Ontario court scrutiny.</p>

          <h3>Cross-Border Asset Division</h3>
          <p>Markham families often hold Chinese real estate, bank deposits, and shareholdings that become contested in divorce. Miao He's dual-licence advantage allows her to assist directly with asset disclosure, investigation of overseas holdings, and enforcement — without referring you to a separate firm.</p>

          <h2>Why Choose a Lawyer Whose Office Is in Markham?</h2>
          <p>The firm is based in Markham. Miao He is familiar with the Superior Court of Justice — Newmarket Courthouse procedures, has working relationships with local mediators and opposing counsel, and understands the cultural context of the community she serves. Local presence means faster response times and deeper practical knowledge of how cases move through this jurisdiction.</p>

          <div class="qa-block">
            <h3>Q: I was divorced in China — do I need to do anything in Canada?</h3>
            <p>A: A Chinese divorce judgment is generally recognized in Canada but requires notarization and authentication. Depending on your situation, you may also need Ontario court recognition. Call 647-930-6688 for a specific assessment.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="qa-block">
            <h3>Q: My spouse and I live in Markham but our assets are in China. Can we litigate in Ontario?</h3>
            <p>A: Yes. Ontario courts have jurisdiction over matrimonial property for Ontario residents — including assets located abroad. Miao He holds dual licences in Ontario and China and can handle cross-border asset matters directly. Call 647-930-6688.</p>
          </div>

